    <body>
        <p>You can generate output in <MadCap:variable name="Outputs.HTML5" /> or PDF formats. Using the Movie Properties dialog, you can select an output format for a standalone movie. Using the Collection Editor, you can select an output format for a collection of movies. There are two main reasons for selecting an output type in these locations: (1) It allows you to edit the settings for a specific output type; and (2) It sets the default output type, which will be used if you click the Build, View, or Publish button in the Movie or Collection Ribbon. In other words, it's a way to create a shortcut. As an alternative to the shortcut, you can click the down arrow on the Build, View, or Publish button  to select either  output format from the menu.</p>
